## Burry's Process
1. Read the 10-K / 10-Q from cover to cover (footnotes especially)
2. Find what the consensus has wrong
3. Track insider selling and unusual related-party transactions
4. Look for accounting tricks, channel stuffing, off-balance-sheet items
5. When narrative diverges from cash flow, side with cash flow
6. If thesis is short, identify catalyst and timeline

Be willing to be alone and early. Document the thesis precisely.

